# Whitelist approach: ignore everything by default, only track skill/task logic (.md) and hand-written source code, never business data, generated output, or credentials
*
!*/
!*.md
!*.md.bak*
!.gitignore

# Source code we actually write (dashboard + automation scripts)
!*.py
!*.js
!*.jsx
!*.ts
!*.tsx
!*.mjs
!*.cjs
!*.mts
!*.cts
!*.html
!*.css
!*.ahk
!*.sh
!*.ps1
!*.bat
!*.cmd

# Extra safety: never track these even if matched above
*.pem
*.key
*.env
.env*
credentials*
*credential*
*token*
*secret*
*password*
brevo_api_key
*.p12
*.pfx

# Generated / dependency / build output -- regenerable, never hand-written, keep out regardless of extension
**/node_modules/
**/__pycache__/
**/.wrangler/
**/.cloudflare/
**/dist/
**/build/
**/.next/
**/.cache/
*.pyc

# Explicit hard excludes: personal health data, financial/tax planning docs, vendored tooling, and generated dashboard snapshot history -- never in git, regardless of extension
Projects/Health Optimization/
Projects/Quickbooks Set UP/
tools/
Projects/Business Dashboard Website/site/artifacts/
Artifacts/

# Hardcoded live eBay production credentials found in these scripts (2026-07-08) -- exclude until refactored to read from the shared untracked credentials file instead of a literal constant
Projects/eBay/ebay_listing_audit.py
Projects/eBay/ebay_caps_fixer.py
Projects/eBay/ebay_jewelry_sold.py
Projects/eBay/ebay_markdown_engine.py
